<head>FINGER</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">手指</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">指</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>MOST MOVING:mobile PART of the HAND.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for a finger and a toe is zhǐ 指 and there are no current competing words.</p>
<p>2. Mǔ 拇 refers both to the thumb and to the big toe.</p>
<p>3. Bò 擘 is frustratingly rare but appears to refer unambiguously to the thumb.</p>
        </div>
